    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix f1star function returning incorrect MAC-S bytes\n\n### Summary\nThe f1star() function in aka_functions.c was returning the wrong 8 bytes for MAC-S calculation. Instead of returning the first 8 bytes of the output as per 3GPP specification, it was returning the second 8 bytes (out1[i+8] instead of out1[i]). This caused authentication failures during resynchronization procedures.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/API/USIM/aka_functions.c`: Fixed f1star function to return correct bytes\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/API/USIM/aka_functions.c`: Added f1* specific constant handling\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Configure UE with USIM authentication parameters\n2. Trigger an authentication resynchronization procedure\n3. Observe that MAC-S validation fails at the network side\n4. Capture the authentication vectors and verify that MAC-S bytes 8-15 are being used instead of bytes 0-7\n\nThe incorrect MAC-S values cause authentication rejects and prevent UE from successfully registering with the network during resync scenarios.\n"
}